--------------
INVISIBLE v1.0
--------------
--------------

	Invisible man is a simple board game written in AMOS. A board is the 
matrix of 12*12 cells filled by various icons. The player must take certain 
number of basic icons to open door and escape through the door to another 
level.  In your quest, you must be careful because some icons may slow 
down or kill.

OPTIONS
-------

	When you start game, you can see a simple menu. In a menu, you can
control the arrow with joystick (up, down and fire) or arrow keys (up, down
and return). Options are:
		
	START GAME

	EASY, MEDIUM or HIGH

	MUSIC or SFX
	
	TOP TEN
	
	HELP
		
	ABOUT

Back to dos is with Del key.

CONTROLS
--------------------

	Controling is with a joystick only. It has two way to operate:

		1. all eight directions (without fire button)
					&
		2. only four directions (with fire button)


SPECIAL KEYS
------------

	Key		Description
      -----------------------------------------------------------------
	 p              pause (any other key or fire button -> return)
	 m              toggle music/sfx
	Esc             interrupt a game, back to the menu
       h/Help           showing where you are 

ICONS
-----
	There are 35 icons in three types existing in this game:
1. type brings bonus points.

	Point, Treasure, 2 gold coin, 5 gold coins, 10 gold coins, Bonus,
	Crown, Ring.

2. type of icons are tools or weapons. With tools or weapons you can kill
   creatures from 3. type.

	Sword, Open gate, Water, Heart, Clock, Shield, Key, Candle,
	Antidote, Ladder. 

3. type mostly slow down or kill you.

	Prison, Cross, Close Gate, Fire, Poison, Death, Wall, Hole, Live
	sand, Black ,Red, Bronze and Gold knight, Darkness, Web, Mouse, Bad
	point.

Details in the game in help option.

TIME
----

	Every level must be finished in certain time. At the beginning of 
the game, time passes very slow, but in every next level, time will be 
accelerated. With clock icon you fill time-left to maximum.


HISCORE
-------

	In the game, hiscore is top ten. List of the best 10. Top ten is in
Inv.top. If Inv.dat doesn't exist, a game will create it.

 

INSTALLATION AND BEGINNING
--------------------------

If you have hard disk, save decompressed files of Invisible in your own 
created directory and type: assign Invisible: your directory.
Example ( if your directory is called games/invisible on dh0: ):

	assign Invisible: dh0:games/invisible

Else create boot disk named Invisible: and save decompressed files to disk.
Invisible require OS 1.3 with 1 MB at least, diskfont.library and
my Invisible.Fonts.
The game was tested on Amiga 500 and Amiga 1200.
